# .trivyignore — accepted / false-positive CVE findings with justification.
# Each entry must include a justification comment explaining the risk acceptance.
# Regenerate with: trivy image --severity CRITICAL --ignore-unfixed <image>

# CVE-2026-22184: zlib CRITICAL in nginx:1.27-alpine3.21 (installed: 1.3.1-r2, fixed: 1.3.2-r0)
# Justification: Fix exists in Alpine package repo but nginx official image has not yet been
# rebuilt with updated packages. nginx:1.27-alpine is a static serving container with no
# user-supplied compressed input; zlib is only used internally by nginx for gzip responses.
# Track: update Dockerfile to nginx:1.27-alpine3.22 (or later) once zlib 1.3.2-r0 is bundled.
CVE-2026-22184
